Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.78,0:00:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, I am Bob Tabor with www.learnvisualstudio.net.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.52,0:00:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lesson we will begin learning about the XAML syntax.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.10,0:00:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly it's pretty easy to figure out the absolute basis of XAML just by looking at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.75,0:00:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean I can imagine that whatever you saw in the previous lesson
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.65,0:00:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you were able to at least figure out the correlation between the tags,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.25,0:00:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the properties and what you saw in the visual designer, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.65,0:00:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well what I want to accomplish is to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.65,0:00:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the features and functions that may not be so obvious at the first glance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.20,0:00:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So we will take a couple of parts at this short videos
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.70,0:00:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,that when combined together will give a pretty throughout understanding of XAML
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.12,0:00:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and how it all works .
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.32,0:00:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In this first lesson we are gonna talk about the purpose and the nature of XAML,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.72,0:00:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,especially in comparison to C#.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.10,0:00:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the next few lessons
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.97,0:00:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we are going to talk about the special features in XAML.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.60,0:01:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Little hidden features of the language that,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.15,0:01:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,again, may not be obvious when you first start looking at it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.30,0:01:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So my aim is that by the end of the first several lessons
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.27,0:01:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to have enough knowledge that you can look at the XAML that we write together
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.45,0:01:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the remainder of this series you are going to be able to take a pretty good guess of what it's trying to do
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.50,0:01:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,before I even explain what it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.30,0:01:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so first of all let's talk about what XAML is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.17,0:01:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In the previous lesson I made a passing remark about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.24,0:01:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how XAML looks similar to HTML and that's no accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.24,0:01:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,XAML is really just XML, the eXtensible Markup Language.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.06,0:01:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I will explained that relationship in just a moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.31,0:01:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but at a higher level
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.95,0:01:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,XML looks a lot like HTML and so much that they share a common ancestry.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.73,0:01:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Whereas HTML is specific to structuring a web page document
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.13,0:01:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,XML a little bit more generic in nature
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.97,0:01:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and by generic I mean that you can use it for any purpose that you decide
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.31,0:02:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can define the names and the elements of the attributes to suit your needs
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.44,0:02:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the past developers have used XML for things like storing application settings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.62,0:02:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or using it as a means of transferring data between two systems that were never intend to work together
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.48,0:02:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And to use XML you start off by defining what's called the schema
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.24,0:02:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,which declares the proper names of the elements and their attributes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.75,0:02:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and so schema is kind of like a contract that two parties agreed to,everybody agrees
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.08,0:02:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Both the producer of XML and the consumer of XML
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.80,0:02:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to write and read the XML to conform to those rules set forth in the contract,I mean, the schema.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.33,0:02:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And now that they both agree
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.20,0:02:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that they're working in the same rule of the same contract and communicate with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.93,0:02:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So, a schema is a really important part of XML
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.13,0:02:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and just keep in mind 'cuz we will come back to that in just a moment
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.51,0:02:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,XAML is a special usage of XML
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.93,0:02:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Obviously we see, at least in this case
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.37,0:03:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,XAML has something to do with defining a user interface for our for application
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.20,0:03:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,so now we got it feels a lot like HTML but there's a big difference
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.42,0:03:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,XAML is actually used to create instances of classes and set values of their properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.40,0:03:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So for example in the previous lesson we created a little hello world application
